\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 17.             Halopeplis}                Bunge ex Ung.-Sternb.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By P.W. Ball.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annual herbs. Leaves alternate, subglobose and amplexicaul with rudimentary lamina. Inflorescence spicate, with a 3-flowered cyme in the axil of each bract. Flowers hermaphrodite or female, more or less connate with each other and with the surrounding bracts. Perianth-segments 3. Stamens 1 or 2. Stigmas 2.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. amplexicaulis} (Vahl) Ung.-Sternb. ex Cesati, Passer. & Gibelli, {\i Comp. Fl. Ital.} 271 (1874) ({\i Halostachys perfoliata} sensu Willk.). Stem erect, 5-30 cm, glaucous, with stout base. Leaves distant; lamina c. 2 mm. Spikes 5-15 mm; bracts ovate-orbicular. Seeds c. 0·5 mm, with cylindrical papillae.{\i  Salt-marshes. S. Europe from S.E. Portugal to S. Italy.} Hs It Lu Sa Si.
\par

