\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 18.             Halostachys}                  C.A. Meyer
\par  

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By P.W. Ball.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Shrubs or small trees. Leaves opposite, connate, with a rudimentary lamina. Inflorescence spicate, with 3-flowered cymes in the axils of opposite, free bracts. Flowers free, hermaphrodite. Perianth-segments 3. Stamen 1. Stigmas 2 or 3.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. belangeriana} (Moq.) Botsch.,{\i  Not. Syst.} ({\i Leningrad}) {\b 16:} 84 (1954) ({\i H. caspica} auct., {\i H. caspia} C.A. Meyer, {\i Halocnemum caspicum} Bieb. pro parte, {\i Arthrocnemum belangerianum} Moq.,{\i  Salicornia caspica} sensu Pallas, non L.). Shrub or small tree up to 3·5 m with erect branched trunk; ultimate branches articulated. Spikes 1-3 cm. Bracts more or less orbicular, slightly cordate. Seeds 0·5-1 mm. {\i Salt-marshes. W. Kazakhstan}. Rs(E). ({\i S.W. & C. Asia.})
\par

